node.text:
Introducing our Autumn-Winter 2021 collection, Seasonal Treasures.

As a testimony to the life we live, our home has a soul of its own. Built around meaningful and carefully chosen objects, it is within these four walls we treasure quiet moments of contemplation. As the season slowly transforms the landscape into a sea of bright reds and yellows, we instinctively begin to cocoon in the comfort of our home.

node.text:
This week we are thrilled to be celebrating the 15th anniversary of ferm LIVING. What initially began as just our founder, Trine Andersen, a bold idea and ten wallpaper designs, has since grown into an established design brand that fuses a Scandinavian mindset with global skills and traditions. 

As ferm LIVING has grown over the years, one thing remains the same: our ambition to inspire people to create a home where they can be comfortably and authentically themselves – a home that embraces you just as you are.

node.text:
This year, Christmas may very well be a smaller, more intimate affair than usual. So now is the perfect opportunity to unleash your creative side with a beautiful, thoughtful table setting that will make your cherished guests feel extra welcome and appreciated while setting the tone for cosy holiday celebrations.

To see more, follow the link in our bio.

node.text: Learn how to make your very own Poppykalas Advent wreath together with Thilde, the founder and creative mind behind @Poppykalas, a Floral Design Studio based in Copenhagen. Her distinctive, pastel-hued creations often take untamed and unexpected forms, at once both delicate and extravagant. In this tutorial, she shares a step by step guide as to how you can create a fun and unique Advent decoration with the use of dried flowers and the Bowl Candle Holder from ferm LIVING.

node.title: Poppykalas: How to Make Your Own Advent Wreath

node.text: A talk between Trine Andersen, Founder and Creative Director of ferm LIVING, and Julie @vonsperling, a hospitality expert with 20 years of experience from the world's leading hotels. Held during 3daysofdesign at the Home of ferm LIVING in Copenhagen.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on September 15, 2021.

node.text: True beauty is often found in nature. Our Oyster Bowl is originally casted in 100% brass from a real oyster shell. With its beautiful, organic details, the bowl offers a decorative place to store burnt matches, jewellery or other precious little knick knacks.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on September 14, 2021. May be an image of furniture and living room.

node.text: Add some softness and texture to your living room space using our new Crease Rug and Cushion. Drawing inspiration from the clean lines found in modern architecture, the Crease Wool Rug and Cushion make a statement with their graphic expression. Handwoven from New Zealand wool, both are tufted in an intricate pattern for a decorative, contemporary look.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on September 13, 2021. Explore the program and visit us in our Boutique and Showroom to get a first ook at our Autumn- Winter 2021 News "Seasonal Treasures" ferm LIVING'.

node.text:
We are excited to welcome you into the Home of ferm LIVING during @3daysofdesign, where we have planned an amazing program filled with interesting talks and activities. 

Swipe through the images to explore the entire program. 
​
​We look forward to seeing you at our historic brand house in Copenhagen.

node.text: Doubling as a lamp and a beautiful, decorative object, the Vuelta Lamp is characterised by its sculptural arc reminiscent of ancient columns. It's made from opal glass with a rippled surface that lends a characteristic, textural appeal to the piece while emitting a pleasant and cosy light.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on September 11, 2021. May be an image of coffee cup.

node.text: Soft, calm textures and beautiful shadows. Come and experience the ferm LIVING universe and the new Autumn-Winter collection at the @fermlivingboutique in the heart of Copenhagen. Open Mondays-Fridays, 10-18, and Saturdays from 10-16.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on September 10, 2021. May be an image of indoor.

node.text:
We are excited to welcome the Curvature Paper Towel Holder to the Curvature family. Available in brass and black brass, it has a curvy, sculptural expression that works perfectly as a decorative storage solution for your everyday paper towels. Crafted by hand, no two pieces are identical.
​
​Available to purchase now.

node.text:
Have you had a chance to browse the pages of our new Autumn-Winter catalogue yet? 

As the season slowly transforms the landscape into a sea of bright reds and yellows, we instinctively begin to cocoon in the comfort of our home. It is within these four walls that you have space to feel comfortably you. 

Follow the link in bio to explore the new Seasonal Treasures catalogue.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on September 08, 2021. May be an image of table and indoor.

node.text:
The Desert Dining Chair - a foldable, elegant seating solution with a simple, modernist profile. Suitable for both indoor and outdoor use, the frame is crafted from tubular, powder coated steel, while the seat is made entirely from recycled post-consumer plastic that has been spun into PET yarn. The fold-up function ensures that the Desert Dining Chair can easily and efficiently be stored away when not in use.
​
​Available for purchase now.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on September 07, 2021. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: Nothing lets you organise your thoughts, inspiration, and ideas like a good pinboard. Our Scenery Pinboard is now available with an elegant oak frame. With its beige, cotton linen fabric on a cork base, the pinboard has a raw and natural look that fits nicely in a modern home. Mount your Scenery Pinboard onto an empty wall, or let it lean up against it for a more casual look.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on September 06, 2021.

node.text:
The mouthblown Water Swirl Vase recalls a whirl of cascading liquid. With its translucent glass, the vase achieves a light and effortless, almost dancing, expression despite being crafted from solid, massive glass. Fill the vase with flowers or stalks, or style it solo and enjoy how the sun filters through the transparent glass. With unique twists and curves, no two vases are identical.
​
​Available for purchase now.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on September 05, 2021. May be an image of indoor.

node.text:
Reminiscent of oyster shells gathered at the beach, the texture and finish of our Oyster Wall Lamp have a distinctive, rough expression. The lamp is cast in recycled aluminium, and the interplay between its curved shape and raw surface creates a compelling, artful contrast. Designed with an LED light source, the Oyster Wall Lamp plays with light and shadow to highlight the uniqueness of the material as well as its organic shape.
​
Available for purchase in October.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ferm LIVING on September 04, 2021.

node.text:
Introducing our Pond collection in Dark Chrome. The Pond collection explores organic shapes for a classic mirror. Inspired by free-flowing movements of water, Pond invites open and fluid forms into your home, turning the functional mirror into a decorative object. Available in different sizes, the mirror can be used in various ways so that you can find the perfect fit for your home.
​
​Available for purchase now.
